132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1749
H.P. 1167 House of Representatives, April 22, 2025
Resolve, Directing the Department of Corrections to Study
Achieving Gender Equality
Reference to the Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety suggested and ordered
printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative MACIAS of Topsham.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Sec. 1. Department of Corrections to study achieving gender equality.
2 Resolved: That the Department of Corrections shall study the extent of gender inequality
3 present in the programs, services, facilities and policies administered or overseen by the
4 department and shall report its findings to the Joint Standing Committee on Criminal
5 Justice and Public Safety by December 3, 2025. The report must include potential solutions
6 for eliminating gender inequality in those areas, including, but not limited to, the
7 construction or redesignation of current facilities and the reallocation of resources,
8 programs and opportunities. The joint standing committee may report out a bill to the
9 Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature based on the report.
10 SUMMARY
1111 This resolve directs the Department of Corrections to study the extent of gender
1122 inequality present in the programs, services, facilities and policies administered or overseen
1133 by the department and recommend potential solutions to the Joint Standing Committee on
1144 Criminal Justice and Public Safety for eliminating gender inequality in those areas by
1155 December 3, 2025.
